physical_examinations.relevant_findings: 2.5 Ã— 1.0-cm yellow plaque with 3 overlying erythematous pedunculated masses on the posterior scalp. Skull films revealed no underlying bony involvement. A complete blood cell count was within normal limits. Biopsy revealed multiple sebaceous glands within the superficial papillary dermis, with increased mucin and increased numbers of ectatic vessels. Areas of extramedullary hematopoiesis, immature adipose tissue, and lipoblasts were identified.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: At 4 months, the immature adipose and hematopoietic elements, as well as the vascular changes, had resolved.
